** The Opportunity **   
We are looking for a motivated and enthusiastic Graduate, committed to
developing their career in our Digital Transformation Program for the Hastings
Deering 2025 Graduate Intake.  
  
  
  
Embark on a transformative journey with the Hastings Deering Graduate Program,
where passion meets potential. This is not just any program; it's your ticket
to sculpting a remarkable engineering career within a global powerhouse. Over
the course of two exhilarating years, you'll be immersed in genuine hands-on
experiences, tackling real projects, and gaining unprecedented exposure to
every facet of the Digital Function. Picture yourself contributing to the
success of one of Caterpillar dealers, making waves and shaping the future of
digital excellence. The adventure begins now-Build Something Big and ignite
your career with us.  
  
** Program Overview **   

  * Commence January 2025 with other Graduates in your cohort. 
  * Two-year program with cross-functional business exposure 
  * Work in a truly agile environment in a leading Digital Transformation Program 
  * Structured rotations across the digital landscape, including but not limited to product management, design and customer experience, data and analytics, business analysis, automation, solution architectures, application development and much more. 
  * Develop networks and friendships through graduate sponsored activities. 
  * Coaching, mentoring and professional skill development. 
  * On the job training and education - apply your tertiary studies to real life experience! 
  * Opportunity to travel. 

  
  
** About You **   

  * Recent graduate (0-3 years) or expected to graduate in 2024. 
  * You will have a growth mindset, passion for customer experience and data along with a genuine interest in digital products and services. 
  * University qualification in Business/ Commerce, Information Technology, Design (CX, UX and/or UI), Data & Analytics, Engineering, or related discipline 
  * Adaptive with the ability to work in a fast-paced agile environment. 
  * Exceptional problem solving and organisational skills. 
  * Committed to developing your career in Engineering at Hastings Deering 

  
  
  
** About the Benefits **   
Hastings Deering offers a wide range of benefits including:  

  * Permanent placement at the end of your Graduate program 
  * Training and support for a rewarding career with diverse opportunities 
  * A culture of inspiration, innovation and collaboration 
  * A competitive remuneration package. 
  * Employee Assistance Program for employees and their families 
  * Discounts on private health, vehicles, travel, retail outlets and more 
  * A culture of Flexibility and Inclusion 

** Application Requirements **   
  
Applicants must attach their academic transcript (an unofficial transcript is
accepted if graduation is pending). Successful applicants will be invited to
attend an engagement centre, interview and to meet other Graduates and Program
Sponsors in May 2024.  
  
  
  
_ Please note you must have citizenship or permanent residency in Australia at
the time of application. _  
  
  
